---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Library"
  section="library"
  eyebrow="Library guide"
  description="Create an asset record once, connect it to the right catalog creators, and keep every release easy to identify."
>
  <section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Add a new asset</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-400">An asset is the central record for something you own: its store link, license, creators, files, and release history stay together.</p>

    <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="app-panel p-5"><p class="font-mono text-xs text-indigo-300">1. Create the record</p><p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">Open <a href="/assets/new" class="text-indigo-300 hover:text-indigo-200">New asset</a>, then add a title. Add a description, tags, thumbnail, marketplace and store URL when they help identify the purchase.</p></article>
      <article class="app-panel p-5"><p class="font-mono text-xs text-indigo-300">2. Connect creators</p><p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">Search the Creators field and choose an existing catalog name. For a new name, type it and press Enter; TailCache creates that catalog creator and links it to the asset when you save.</p></article>
      <article class="app-panel p-5"><p class="font-mono text-xs text-indigo-300">3. Save the asset</p><p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">Select Create asset. The detail page is where you add downloadable files, organized under versions rather than attached directly to the asset.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 border-t border-white/10 pt-10">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-indigo-300">Catalog behavior</p>
    <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-semibold text-white">How creators are linked</h2>
    <div class="mt-4 rounded-2xl border border-indigo-400/15 bg-indigo-500/[0.055] p-5 sm:p-6">
      <p class="text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">Creator names are shared catalog records, not private labels. Selecting a match links your asset to it; entering a new name creates a catalog record first, then links your asset to that record. You can associate more than one creator with an asset.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 border-t border-white/10 pt-10">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-indigo-300">Release history</p>
    <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-semibold text-white">How versions work</h2>
    <div class="mt-5 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-white/10">
      <div class="grid divide-y divide-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] sm:grid-cols-[9.5rem_1fr] sm:divide-x sm:divide-y-0"><div class="p-5"><p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-zinc-500">Create</p></div><div class="p-5 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">On the asset detail page, select <strong class="font-medium text-white">Add Version</strong>. Give it a unique version name, such as <code class="rounded bg-black/25 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs text-indigo-200">1.0</code> or <code class="rounded bg-black/25 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs text-indigo-200">2026.07</code>, and add optional release notes.</div></div>
      <div class="grid divide-y divide-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] sm:grid-cols-[9.5rem_1fr] sm:divide-x sm:divide-y-0"><div class="p-5"><p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-zinc-500">Upload</p></div><div class="p-5 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">Upload one or more files inside that version. This keeps installers, source files, and notes for a release together while older releases remain easy to find.</div></div>
      <div class="grid divide-y divide-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] sm:grid-cols-[9.5rem_1fr] sm:divide-x sm:divide-y-0"><div class="p-5"><p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-zinc-500">Update</p></div><div class="p-5 text-sm leading-6 text-zinc-300">For a later release, add another version instead of replacing the record. Version names must be unique within an asset. Creator-linked copies are updated by syncing from the creator, so they do not accept local versions.</div></div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
